Therefore, a rational CO2 photoreduction mechanistic pathway catalyzed by TMOF-10-NH2(I) is proposed: (1) CO2 and H2O are initially adsorbed on the catalyst surface. (2) Subsequently, the adsorbed *CO2 molecules interact with the surface protons to form the *COOH intermediate upon illumination. (3) The deprotonation of *COOH intermediate gives the *CO molecules, while the proton transfer affords the absorbed H2O on MOFs into H2O2. Based on the spectroscopy investigations, the possible reaction pathway of overall solar CO2 reduction could be proposed as follows:3CO2(g)→CO2*\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
