To determine the water oxidation product, the volume of H2O was increased to 30 mL, while the other conditions were kept to be the same as before. Every 4 h, 1 mL of the liquid was sampled for quantitative measurement, and the system was refilled with CO2. To confirm the production and accumulation of H2O2, the concentration of H2O2 was quantified by colorimetry and DPD/POD method, respectively60.
For the colorimetry method, the amount of H2O2 in the liquid phase was measured by UV-Vis spectra according to the color changes from Fe2+ to Fe3+ at wavelength of 330 nm as shown in the following equation:11Fe2++H2O2+H+→Fe3++2H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
